real estate bubbles.

142
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:29,980
Stock market bubbles.

143
00:04:29,980 --> 00:04:31,500
And, naturally,

144
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,600
fish bladder bubbles.

145
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,940
It's like Chinese investors looked at

146
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:36,370
the Dutch tulip bulb craze,

147
00:04:36,370 --> 00:04:37,370
and thought,

148
00:04:37,370 --> 00:04:38,370
what a great idea,

149
00:04:38,370 --> 00:04:40,600
but it needs more fish bladders.

150
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,720
Putting your money in an online cryptocurrency

151
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,900
stored on something called a blockchain

152
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:47,060
that can do something called forking

153
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:48,060
doesn't seem so crazy

154
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,320
now, does it?

155
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:52,180
Hmmm...Bitcoin or fish bladders?

156
00:04:52,180 --> 00:04:54,280
Which will be the money of the future?

157
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:56,240
Anyway, speculation,

158
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,280
no matter the medium,

159
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,220
has the same result.

160
00:04:59,220 --> 00:05:00,260
And many of the same things

161
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:02,590
that led to China's stock market collapse

162
00:05:02,590 --> 00:05:06,070
are now happening in China's Bitcoin exchanges:

163
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,070
People dipping in and out

164
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:08,260
to make a quick buck,

165
00:05:08,260 --> 00:05:10,139
leading to wild market fluctuations,

166
00:05:10,139 --> 00:05:12,280
