by the Chinese regime.

175
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,570
Uhhhh....about that.

176
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:31,071
The third reason the Chinese Communist Party

177
00:05:31,071 --> 00:05:33,639
has been targeting Bitcoin is control.

178
00:05:33,639 --> 00:05:37,120
You see, the CCP is not out to kill Bitcoin—

179
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,740
at least not right now.

180
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:42,139
They just want to bend Bitcoin to their advantage.

181
00:05:42,139 --> 00:05:44,620
But first, let’s talk about Bitcoin mining.

182
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:45,780
Simply put,

183
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:47,150
people can run powerful computers

184
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:49,330
to solve complex math problems

185
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:51,990
that validate Bitcoin transactions--

186
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:52,990
that's the cryptography

187
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:54,639
I was mentioning earlier--

188
00:05:54,639 --> 00:05:56,800
and they're rewarded with Bitcoins.

189
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:59,240
This is how new Bitcoins are created.

190
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,370
But nowadays Bitcoin mining

191
00:06:00,370 --> 00:06:02,010
requires powerful computers,

192
00:06:02,010 --> 00:06:03,240
custom chips,

193
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:05,390
and lots of electricity.

194
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:06,390
And it turns out

195
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:08,730
China is home to 50 to 70 percent

196
00:06:08,730 --> 00:06:11,520
of the world’s Bitcoin mining operations.

197
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:12,889
The Chinese government could, of course,

198
00:06:12,889 --> 00:06:14,200
restrict Bitcoin mining,

199
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,520
but it doesn’t.

200
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:16,840
Quite the opposite.

201
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:17,840
In many instances

202
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:20,420
the government is actively supporting it.

203
00:06:20,420 --> 00:06:22,240
According to Bitcoin Magazine,

204
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,669
major Bitcoin mines in China’s northwest

205
